target: renderer
validations:
  - name: layer_rendering_order
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify the render function draws layers in the exact order specified:
        (1) ground tiles, (2) enclosure fills, (3) enclosure borders, (4) path overlay,
        (5) animals sorted by y-coordinate, (6) visitors sorted by y-coordinate,
        (7) build ghost if in building mode, (8) UI overlays (HUD, sidebar, info bar,
        tooltips, toasts), (9) mini-map. Each category must be fully drawn before the
        next begins. Animals and visitors must be y-sorted to give correct visual overlap.

  - name: camera_bounds_clamping
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify the camera position is clamped so it never shows area outside the map.
        The minimum camera x and y must be 0. The maximum camera x must be
        (MAP_COLS * TILE_SIZE - VIEWPORT_WIDTH) and maximum y must be
        (MAP_ROWS * TILE_SIZE - VIEWPORT_HEIGHT). If the map is smaller than the
        viewport in either dimension, the camera should be locked to 0 on that axis.
        Smooth scrolling must use interpolation (lerp) toward a target, not jump directly.

  - name: viewport_culling
    type: agent_validation
    severity: warning
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify the ground tile drawing loop only iterates over tiles visible in the
        current viewport, not all 40*30=1200 tiles. The start/end column and row
        should be calculated from the camera position and viewport dimensions.
        Off-screen tiles must not have any draw calls executed for them.

  - name: minimap_rendering
    type: agent_validation
    severity: warning
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify a mini-map is rendered in the bottom-right area of the main viewport
        (not overlapping the sidebar). It should be approximately 80x60 pixels, showing
        the full map with 2px per tile. Enclosures should be drawn on the mini-map in
        their biome color. A white rectangle should indicate the current camera viewport
        position on the mini-map.

  - name: build_ghost_preview
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify that when the input mode is 'building' and the mouse hovers over the map,
        a semi-transparent preview of the enclosure is drawn at the hover position. The
        preview must use reduced opacity (alpha ~0.4). If the placement is invalid, an
        additional red overlay must indicate the invalid placement. The ghost must follow
        the cursor in real time and disappear when build mode is exited.
